  {
    "slug": "responsible-waste-disposal-policy",
    "title": "Responsible Waste Disposal Policy | Cornwall Waste Clearance",
    "body_content": "<section class=\"content-section\">\n  <div class=\"container content-narrow\">\n\n    <h2>Our Commitment</h2>\n    <p>Cornwall Waste Clearance is committed to disposing of all waste in a responsible, legal and environmentally conscious manner. We are a licensed waste carrier, registered with the Environment Agency, and we take our environmental obligations seriously.</p>\n\n    <h2>Licensed Waste Carrier</h2>\n    <p>We are fully registered with the Environment Agency as a licensed waste carrier. This means you can be confident that every item we remove from your property is handled and disposed of in full compliance with UK waste regulations.</p>\n    <p>It is illegal to use an unlicensed waste carrier. Always ask to see proof of registration before hiring any clearance company.</p>\n\n    <h2>Recycling First</h2>\n    <p>Wherever possible, we sort and segregate waste so that materials can be recycled. We aim to divert as much as possible away from landfill by working with local recycling centres and approved waste transfer stations in Cornwall.</p>\n\n    <h2>Charity Donations</h2>\n    <p>Items that are still in good usable condition \u2014 furniture, clothing, appliances and household goods \u2014 are offered to local charities and reuse organisations rather than being discarded. This reduces waste and benefits the local community.</p>\n\n    <h2>Hazardous Waste</h2>\n    <p>Certain items require specialist disposal and cannot be handled as general waste. These include:</p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Asbestos-containing materials</li>\n      <li>Refrigerants and items containing CFCs (fridges, freezers, air conditioning units)</li>\n      <li>Paints, solvents and chemicals</li>\n      <li>Batteries and electrical waste (WEEE)</li>\n    </ul>\n    <p>We will advise you at the point of quotation if any items require specialist disposal and whether additional charges apply.</p>\n\n    <h2>Fly-Tipping</h2>\n    <p>We have a zero-tolerance policy on fly-tipping. All waste collected is transported to licensed disposal or transfer facilities. We never dump waste illegally, and we will not accept jobs where we suspect waste will be used to facilitate illegal dumping.</p>\n\n    <h2>Our Environmental Goal</h2>\n    <p>We continuously review our processes to reduce our environmental footprint \u2014 from the routes we plan to the facilities we use. We are committed to improving our recycling rates year on year.</p>\n\n    <h2>Contact Us</h2>\n    <p>If you have any questions about how we handle waste, please call us on <a href=\"tel:07347300788\">07347 300788</a> or visit our <a href=\"/contact-us/\">contact page</a>.</p>\n\n  </div>\n</section>",
    "description": "Cornwall Waste Clearance is committed to responsible, legal and eco-friendly waste disposal across Cornwall. Read our full policy here."
  },
